# Cleanup Standards

Automated enforcement: `./gradlew detekt ktlintCheck` must pass before any commit.

## No Magic Numbers

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
if (batteryLevel < 15) switchToSurvivalMode()
if (riders.size > 4) enableClustering()
val interval = 5000L

// ✅ GOOD -- named constants in RouteConstants or feature-specific companion object
object SlickConstants {
    const val SURVIVAL_MODE_BATTERY_THRESHOLD = 15
    const val CONVOY_CLUSTERING_THRESHOLD = 4
    const val BLE_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000L
    const val NODE_INTERVAL_KM = 10.0
    const val MAX_DETOUR_RADIUS_KM = 15.0
    const val THERMAL_THROTTLE_CELSIUS = 40.0
    const val THERMAL_CRITICAL_CELSIUS = 45.0
    const val SOS_COUNTDOWN_SECONDS = 60
    const val GPS_BATCH_SURVIVAL_MS = 30_000L
    const val PACK_BROADCAST_INTERVAL_MS = 5_000L   // 0.2 Hz
    const val LEAD_BROADCAST_INTERVAL_MS = 1_000L    // 1 Hz
}
```

## No Hardcoded URLs or IDs

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
val url = "https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast"
val serviceId = "com.slick.tactical.mesh.v1"

// ✅ GOOD -- from BuildConfig (injected via secrets-gradle-plugin)
val baseUrl = BuildConfig.OPEN_METEO_BASE_URL
val serviceId = BuildConfig.P2P_SERVICE_ID
```

## Timber Only -- No Raw Logging

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED everywhere
Log.d("TAG", "message")
Log.e("TAG", "error", exception)
println("debug info")
System.out.println("something")

// ✅ REQUIRED
Timber.d("Node loaded: %s", nodeId)
Timber.e(exception, "Sync failed for convoy: %s", convoyId)
```

Timber is initialized in `SlickApplication.onCreate()` for debug builds only.

## KDoc on All Public Functions

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- undocumented public API
fun haversineDistance(lat1: Double, lon1: Double, lat2: Double, lon2: Double): Double

// ✅ GOOD
/**
 * Calculates great-circle distance between two GPS coordinates.
 * Uses the Haversine formula with Earth radius = 6371.0 km.
 *
 * @return Distance in kilometres
 */
fun haversineDistance(lat1: Double, lon1: Double, lat2: Double, lon2: Double): Double
```

## No Empty Files

Files with 0 lines or only `package` declaration should be deleted.

## No Duplicate Utilities

Before creating a new utility function, search for existing:
- `util/Haversine.kt` -- distance calculations
- `util/MetricConverter.kt` -- unit conversions
- `util/ResultExtensions.kt` -- Result<T> helpers
- `util/TimeFormatter.kt` -- 24h time formatting

## File Size Enforcement

Check with detekt or manual review:

| Type | Max Lines | Violation Action |
|------|-----------|-----------------|
| Service | 400 | Extract engine component |
| Composable screen | 250 | Extract sub-composables |
| ViewModel | 300 | Extract use case classes |
| Repository | 300 | Split by data source |
| Engine Manager | 400 | Extract strategy classes |
| Utility | 150 | Split by concern |

## Pre-Commit Checklist

Run before every git commit:
```bash
./gradlew ktlintCheck          # Kotlin style
./gradlew detekt               # Static analysis
./gradlew test                 # Unit tests
./gradlew assembleDebug        # Build check
```
